<subSubSection id="6EC5B943BD2E3531F5623613FD9F93C3" pageId="0" pageNumber="11" type="type material">
<paragraph id="B3AE701F048CB943D4681C3D0C62444A" pageId="0" pageNumber="11">Type material.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="67C45C72B084F2A960BCAA7C092E9A50" pageId="0" pageNumber="11">
Holotype, ♀ (ZJUH), &quot;NE China: Shandong, Shanghe County, 
<normalizedToken id="014951A45A366303B3B947AE3E5EC5A5" originalValue="Ji’nan">Ji'nan</normalizedToken>
, Xushang, Dong Balizhuang, 
<geoCoordinate id="9EFC3CC104305ECEDF47A3B9C0336733" degrees="36" direction="north" minutes="16" orientation="latitude" precision="15" seconds="4" value="36.267776">36°16'4&quot;N</geoCoordinate>
, 
<geoCoordinate id="06FDD3ADBD385391E90EAFDE061BCED0" degrees="117" direction="east" minutes="9" orientation="longitude" precision="15" seconds="10" value="117.15278">117°9'10&quot;E</geoCoordinate>
, Malaise trap, 24-30.ix.2018, Jia-He Yan &amp; Qi-Meng Yang&quot;, Paratypes (ZJUH, RMNH): 40 ♀, same data as holotype, of which 1 ♀ (ZJUH) additionally labelled 
<normalizedToken id="1C4C232EADE886CDBD469D12519E4A93" originalValue="“201901120”">&quot;201901120&quot;</normalizedToken>
, because the molecular sequences originate from this specimen.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="CFEF24DEB84670F750950093D756337D" pageId="0" pageNumber="11" type="differentiating diagnosis">
<paragraph id="5800540E0690141DA6A91DFE365DF80F" pageId="0" pageNumber="11">Differentiating diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="2800917B860F2C6E497F0849766EFA7C" pageId="0" pageNumber="11">
The new species is similar to the SW Palaearctic 
<taxonomicName id="BBB05503D760DFF0043C0DA3A18503BA" genus="H." lsidName="H. juncoi" pageId="0" pageNumber="11" rank="species" species="juncoi">
<emphasis id="9493D641A9ABB43850106EB644269BF5" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="11">H. juncoi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Ceballos, 1957), because of the largely glabrous basal cell of the fore wing, vein 1-M of fore wing as dark as vein 2-CU1 of fore wing, ivory scutellum (except medio-anteriorly), larger body size and anterior notaulic area of mesoscutum more or less ivory or brownish. 
<bibRefCitation id="D28F4249EC4BA6A5B9D68E7B8839BE58" DOI="https://doi.org/10.1111/j.1748-5967.2011.00352.x" author="Konishi, K" journalOrPublisher="Entomological Research" pageId="0" pageNumber="11" pagination="19 - 27" refId="B13" refString="Konishi, K, Choi, M-B, Lee, J-W, 2012. Review of the East Asian species of the genera Hybrizon Fallen and Ghilaromma Tobias (Hymenoptera: Ichneumonidae: Hybrizontinae). Entomological Research 42: 19 - 27" title="Review of the East Asian species of the genera Hybrizon Fallen and Ghilaromma Tobias (Hymenoptera: Ichneumonidae: Hybrizontinae)." url="https://doi.org/10.1111/j.1748-5967.2011.00352.x" volume="42" year="2012">Konishi et al. (2012)</bibRefCitation>
included Korean specimens of this species under 
<taxonomicName id="8671C8C4A2D8F70B9971C343C6AC874C" genus="H." lsidName="H. juncoi" pageId="0" pageNumber="11" rank="species" species="juncoi">
<emphasis id="FDF692D355669F492521B5E0F3C18DF4" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="11">H. juncoi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but 
<taxonomicName id="067859DFEECDD7AC74F18906351036A6" genus="H." lsidName="H. juncoi" pageId="0" pageNumber="11" rank="species" species="juncoi">
<emphasis id="A47425178E26DA8ECD9C4899C563F5B2" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="11">H. juncoi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has the hind basitarsus about 4.5 times longer than wide (both sexes; 5.6-6.8 times in 
<taxonomicName id="1BF114153F7693102AAC34FE3BC25B20" genus="H." lsidName="H. xui" pageId="0" pageNumber="11" rank="species" species="xui">
<emphasis id="13AC417F037253B739408F316A41AFC0" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="11">H. xui</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), vein r of fore wing issued comparatively far removed from base of pterostigma (distance to base of pterostigma about equal to length of vein r; much less so in 
<taxonomicName id="12B36A64AFC0FB6739C149AEC0EA74EC" genus="H." lsidName="H. xui" pageId="0" pageNumber="11" rank="species" species="xui">
<emphasis id="68F6C6E7F7355C3CFD82A97F746DBA5D" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="11">H. xui</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), propodeum distinctly rugose-granulate (granulate and partly smooth in 
<taxonomicName id="B5409F6F8BDC03A079CEA3AF741C6456" genus="H." lsidName="H. xui" pageId="0" pageNumber="11" rank="species" species="xui">
<emphasis id="A98E40981A8FBF24DF64C332FAE7D66C" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="11">H. xui</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), vein 1-M comparatively short (fig. 41 in 
<bibRefCitation id="3E9AB28AD1F11C1DC6212233C55E41A9" author="van Achterberg, C" journalOrPublisher="Zoologische Mededelingen Leiden" pageId="0" pageNumber="11" pagination="11 - 26" refId="B22" refString="van Achterberg, C, 1999. The West Palaearctic species of the subfamily Paxylommatinae (Hymenoptera: Ichneumonidae), with special reference to the genus Hybrizon Fallen. Zoologische Mededelingen Leiden 73: 11 - 26" title="The West Palaearctic species of the subfamily Paxylommatinae (Hymenoptera: Ichneumonidae), with special reference to the genus Hybrizon Fallen." volume="73" year="1999">van Achterberg 1999</bibRefCitation>
), resulting in a transverse disco-submarginal cell lower than subdiscal cell (vein 1-M medium-sized, resulting in a disco-submarginal cell as high as subdiscal cell in 
<taxonomicName id="C1EF43C44C3FE3227E42C3A2818AD4A3" genus="H." lsidName="H. xui" pageId="0" pageNumber="11" rank="species" species="xui">
<emphasis id="801218043E96AAB9F8DC3254F74B7836" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="11">H. xui</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) and penultimate segment of maxillary palp enlarged (
<figureCitation id="87F412D717B267235451BEBC774AF193" captionStart="Figures 1–8" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figures 1 - 8. 1 - 3 Hybrizon buccatus (de Brebisson) ♀, Bulgaria, Brodilovo, but 3 of ♀ from Netherlands, Nunspeet 4, 5 H. flavofacialis Tobias, female, China, Hunan, Yuanjiang 6, 7 H. ghilarovi Tobias: 6 of ♀, China, Hunan, Yuanjiang and 7 of ♀, Bulgaria, Brodilovo 8 H. juncoi (Ceballos), ♀, Spain, Estepona 1, 4, 6 basal half of fore wing 2, 3, 5 hind basitarsus lateral 7 ovipositor and sheath lateral 8 palpi anterior. From van Achterberg (1999) and van Achterberg et al. (2013)." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.72.39333.figures1-8" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/351486" pageId="0" pageNumber="11" tableDoi="10.3897/jhr.72.39333.figures1-8">Fig. 8</figureCitation>
; small in 
<taxonomicName id="1CDB046437B3AEEEAD9993745CF84617" genus="H." lsidName="H. xui" pageId="0" pageNumber="11" rank="species" species="xui">
<emphasis id="2FF8FBAC2C0CF021553B3CB83B41974B" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="11">H. xui</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). According to the molecular analyses it is distinctly separated from 
<taxonomicName id="A81BCF8060FAF329167DD1EE1B9C6358" genus="H." lsidName="H. hei" pageId="0" pageNumber="11" rank="species" species="hei">
<emphasis id="32CE05642C5B2B77BE7BDB9173EDB514" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="11">H. hei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="73F725FF8A79138124801310B6472BD5" genus="H." lsidName="H. buccatus" pageId="0" pageNumber="11" rank="species" species="buccatus">
<emphasis id="30D154C003AD6CAB39A69313EF21746A" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="11">H. buccatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation id="1CC0355854EDB0D58CFD1AD614CE64EA" captionStart="Figures 30, 31" captionStartId="F5" captionText="Figures 30, 31. RAxML result analysis of 28 S and COI sequences. Numbers in parentheses are GenBank numbers." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.72.39333.figures30-31" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/351490" pageId="0" pageNumber="11" tableDoi="10.3897/jhr.72.39333.figures30-31">Figs 30</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="4A02BDB6760E7025EF43B69491CFDA71" captionStart="Figures 30, 31" captionStartId="F5" captionText="Figures 30, 31. RAxML result analysis of 28 S and COI sequences. Numbers in parentheses are GenBank numbers." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.72.39333.figures30-31" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/351490" pageId="0" pageNumber="11" tableDoi="10.3897/jhr.72.39333.figures30-31">31</figureCitation>
); unfortunately, molecular data of its most closely relative (
<taxonomicName id="289D448795082AD334560A2067862E67" genus="H." lsidName="H. juncoi" pageId="0" pageNumber="11" rank="species" species="juncoi">
<emphasis id="04656D309503121EC24CDD47B10307E3" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="11">H. juncoi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) are yet unknown.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="E8E4CEB26BD8F74435A504D70BF34E71" pageId="0" pageNumber="11" type="molecular data">
<paragraph id="9357079FC31FA7E3805D8AD3305C5B84" pageId="0" pageNumber="11">Molecular data.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="2C728ABA0FFC839E3955C78269BFA566" pageId="0" pageNumber="11">
MN168195 (
<emphasis id="74DC0D4121E2A3D0AE9A883F21F56DDA" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="11">28S</emphasis>
) and MN260327 (
<emphasis id="CCFD5F03C4F109FC2840F372A6852652" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="11">CO1</emphasis>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="42E4C0C86838376E3BF5AEE945B4BBBB" pageId="0" pageNumber="11" type="description">
<paragraph id="C56BABA155403EB52CB3512E4F87CA5E" pageId="0" pageNumber="11">Description.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="BB1BA5E483622E7AB3B084CCD4D3C08E" pageId="0" pageNumber="11">Holotype, ♀, length of body 4.2 mm, of fore wing 3.1 mm.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="C2A0D8D80ADF55974AF67E934BF15B09" pageId="0" pageNumber="11">
<emphasis id="91DAB8511CB6487CF55CAA4AF7C3924F" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="11">
<emphasis id="BFCC33BB2DB2C0278AB2BB6B0AFD044A" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="11">Head</emphasis>
.
</emphasis>
Antenna with 13 segments and 0.9 times as long as fore wing, length of third segment 1.4 times fourth segment, length of third, fourth and penultimate segments 5.3, 3.8 and 3.3 times their width, respectively; pedicellus slightly shorter than and as wide as scapus; penultimate segment of maxillary palp small compared to apical segment (
<figureCitation id="83E716DC2AFC471D30A49DFA0A625E0F" captionStart="Figures 23–29" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figures 23 - 29. Hybrizon xui sp. nov., ♀, paratype 23 habitus, lateral aspect 24 wings 25 hind tarsus, lateral aspect 26 head and mesosoma lateral aspect 27 head, anterior aspect 28 head and mesosoma, dorsal aspect 29 ovipositor and ovipositor sheath, lateral aspect." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.72.39333.figures23-29" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/351489" pageId="0" pageNumber="11" tableDoi="10.3897/jhr.72.39333.figures23-29">Fig. 26</figureCitation>
); face rugulose-granulate medio-dorsally and remainder largely smooth; maximum width of face 1.4 times its minimum width (
<figureCitation id="26F950B8E05A3D02A50AF11D4F4E792B" captionStart="Figures 23–29" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figures 23 - 29. Hybrizon xui sp. nov., ♀, paratype 23 habitus, lateral aspect 24 wings 25 hind tarsus, lateral aspect 26 head and mesosoma lateral aspect 27 head, anterior aspect 28 head and mesosoma, dorsal aspect 29 ovipositor and ovipositor sheath, lateral aspect." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.72.39333.figures23-29" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/351489" pageId="0" pageNumber="11" tableDoi="10.3897/jhr.72.39333.figures23-29">Fig. 27</figureCitation>
); frons smooth and shiny but near antennal sockets depressed and rugulose; length of eye 6.8 times temple in dorsal view; temples directly narrowed behind eyes; vertex shiny and superficially granulate; OOL:diameter of ocellus:POL = 3:5:7; length of malar space 1.3 times basal width of mandible, concave and largely smooth, posteriorly granulate.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="835DB442C0C39904F773064BDAE9E010" pageId="0" pageNumber="11">
<emphasis id="DCE13488CFB4D102F5E565470C02A395" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="11">
<emphasis id="3E1808C1F3BEA9BF5706B1B717BFAC1E" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="11">Mesosoma</emphasis>
.
</emphasis>
Length of mesosoma 1.2 times its height; mesoscutum strongly shiny and smooth, only anteriorly with few punctures and notauli absent (
<figureCitation id="C3E4C515D9992030EB15AB060A35C77C" captionStart="Figures 23–29" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figures 23 - 29. Hybrizon xui sp. nov., ♀, paratype 23 habitus, lateral aspect 24 wings 25 hind tarsus, lateral aspect 26 head and mesosoma lateral aspect 27 head, anterior aspect 28 head and mesosoma, dorsal aspect 29 ovipositor and ovipositor sheath, lateral aspect." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.72.39333.figures23-29" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/351489" pageId="0" pageNumber="11" tableDoi="10.3897/jhr.72.39333.figures23-29">Fig. 28</figureCitation>
); scutellum strongly convex (protruding up to dorsal level of mesoscutum or above) and shiny, smooth (
<figureCitation id="90498FFF386E8E0684D5C66C1E63A24D" captionStart="Figures 23–29" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figures 23 - 29. Hybrizon xui sp. nov., ♀, paratype 23 habitus, lateral aspect 24 wings 25 hind tarsus, lateral aspect 26 head and mesosoma lateral aspect 27 head, anterior aspect 28 head and mesosoma, dorsal aspect 29 ovipositor and ovipositor sheath, lateral aspect." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.72.39333.figures23-29" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/351489" pageId="0" pageNumber="11" tableDoi="10.3897/jhr.72.39333.figures23-29">Figs 26</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="A929C84E5BE4F99925F2247188244CEF" captionStart="Figures 23–29" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figures 23 - 29. Hybrizon xui sp. nov., ♀, paratype 23 habitus, lateral aspect 24 wings 25 hind tarsus, lateral aspect 26 head and mesosoma lateral aspect 27 head, anterior aspect 28 head and mesosoma, dorsal aspect 29 ovipositor and ovipositor sheath, lateral aspect." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.72.39333.figures23-29" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/351489" pageId="0" pageNumber="11" tableDoi="10.3897/jhr.72.39333.figures23-29">28</figureCitation>
); mesopleuron shiny and largely smooth; mesosternal sulcus narrow and smooth; metapleuron shiny and granulate; metanotum obtusely protruding dorsally; propodeum granulate, but medially and posteriorly with some rugae or carinae and interspaces largely smooth.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="2B6AE6E26447366939603DC3ACDB5EF7" pageId="0" pageNumber="11">
<emphasis id="4C657D37F7407D63C533771F3D1FD775" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="11">
<emphasis id="D2313A2870330C0A6CE8596301B3CBCC" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="11">Wings</emphasis>
.
</emphasis>
Fore wing: marginal cell comparatively wide (
<figureCitation id="117EA122A0995BDC27772700E82E8187" captionStart="Figures 23–29" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figures 23 - 29. Hybrizon xui sp. nov., ♀, paratype 23 habitus, lateral aspect 24 wings 25 hind tarsus, lateral aspect 26 head and mesosoma lateral aspect 27 head, anterior aspect 28 head and mesosoma, dorsal aspect 29 ovipositor and ovipositor sheath, lateral aspect." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.72.39333.figures23-29" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/351489" pageId="0" pageNumber="11" tableDoi="10.3897/jhr.72.39333.figures23-29">Fig. 24</figureCitation>
); basal cell of fore wing largely glabrous, with 18 setae (
<figureCitation id="3E466F1B3F9DAB9A1E3AAE55156DBEAF" captionStart="Figures 23–29" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figures 23 - 29. Hybrizon xui sp. nov., ♀, paratype 23 habitus, lateral aspect 24 wings 25 hind tarsus, lateral aspect 26 head and mesosoma lateral aspect 27 head, anterior aspect 28 head and mesosoma, dorsal aspect 29 ovipositor and ovipositor sheath, lateral aspect." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.72.39333.figures23-29" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/351489" pageId="0" pageNumber="11" tableDoi="10.3897/jhr.72.39333.figures23-29">Fig. 24</figureCitation>
); vein r nearly vertical and issued comparatively close to base of pterostigma (
<figureCitation id="BF40757D744D85878349A1B4C6FE6D7E" captionStart="Figures 23–29" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figures 23 - 29. Hybrizon xui sp. nov., ♀, paratype 23 habitus, lateral aspect 24 wings 25 hind tarsus, lateral aspect 26 head and mesosoma lateral aspect 27 head, anterior aspect 28 head and mesosoma, dorsal aspect 29 ovipositor and ovipositor sheath, lateral aspect." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.72.39333.figures23-29" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/351489" pageId="0" pageNumber="11" tableDoi="10.3897/jhr.72.39333.figures23-29">Fig. 24</figureCitation>
); vein 1-R1 0.6 times length of pterostigma; vein 1-M moderately curved and medium-sized, resulting in a disco-submarginal cell as high as subdiscal cell.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="C13AA25E25FACA169574F2EF0EC1E030" pageId="0" pageNumber="11">
<emphasis id="CF98DD36FF2E57E41A7C16BFA8AF7915" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="11">
<emphasis id="9728D24E3C790198C08FCA960FB1FDED" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="11">Legs</emphasis>
.
</emphasis>
Hind coxa finely granulate; in lateral view length of femur, tibia and basitarsus of hind leg 6.9, 6.8 and 5.6 times their width, respectively; spurs of hind tibia 0.35 and 0.40 times hind basitarsus.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="10C4B281020DD9EC08D1D1C6303D54E9" pageId="0" pageNumber="11">
<emphasis id="81D2B184A7CA7E5921E4F448AEADAE79" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="11">
<emphasis id="29A24D876631229E7A0EB0451CA0D2DB" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="11">Metasoma</emphasis>
.
</emphasis>
Length of first tergite 3.4 times its apical width, shiny, smooth (also laterally), medially with shallow elongate depression, subapically widened and its spiracles slightly protruding; second tergite with spaced striae basally and some superficial micro-sculpture medially; remainder of metasoma smooth and shiny; hypopygium with long bristly setae (
<figureCitation id="63046E73B32DD066B39761CA686BB2EA" captionStart="Figures 23–29" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figures 23 - 29. Hybrizon xui sp. nov., ♀, paratype 23 habitus, lateral aspect 24 wings 25 hind tarsus, lateral aspect 26 head and mesosoma lateral aspect 27 head, anterior aspect 28 head and mesosoma, dorsal aspect 29 ovipositor and ovipositor sheath, lateral aspect." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.72.39333.figures23-29" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/351489" pageId="0" pageNumber="11" tableDoi="10.3897/jhr.72.39333.figures23-29">Fig. 29</figureCitation>
); second tergite with sharp lateral crease; length of setose part of ovipositor sheath 0.08 times fore wing and 0.26 times second metasomal tergite.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="3E3784B23A6C2A9A7F70732DEF36FF9D" pageId="0" pageNumber="11">
<emphasis id="C54931DD56FB85558F02BD5A835EADEA" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="11">
<emphasis id="36BAE3B2CB6B614085F9249FAE319509" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="11">Colour</emphasis>
.
</emphasis>
Dark brown; mouthparts (including mandible) and tegulae white; scapus, and scutellum (except medio-anteriorly) ivory; scutellum distinctly contrasting with dark brown mesoscutum medio-posteriorly (
<figureCitation id="1AFB790084A4C0CDA2A3B540EA9643C1" captionStart="Figures 23–29" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figures 23 - 29. Hybrizon xui sp. nov., ♀, paratype 23 habitus, lateral aspect 24 wings 25 hind tarsus, lateral aspect 26 head and mesosoma lateral aspect 27 head, anterior aspect 28 head and mesosoma, dorsal aspect 29 ovipositor and ovipositor sheath, lateral aspect." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.72.39333.figures23-29" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/351489" pageId="0" pageNumber="11" tableDoi="10.3897/jhr.72.39333.figures23-29">Fig. 28</figureCitation>
); mesoscutum antero-laterally, pronotum, mesosternum, mesopleuron dorsally and ventrally, anterior half of fourth tergite and legs yellowish brown; pedicellus entirely brown and distinctly contrasting with pale scapus (
<figureCitation id="15E29CF0BA0A18CEF337273B4E80F3C0" captionStart="Figures 23–29" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figures 23 - 29. Hybrizon xui sp. nov., ♀, paratype 23 habitus, lateral aspect 24 wings 25 hind tarsus, lateral aspect 26 head and mesosoma lateral aspect 27 head, anterior aspect 28 head and mesosoma, dorsal aspect 29 ovipositor and ovipositor sheath, lateral aspect." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.72.39333.figures23-29" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/351489" pageId="0" pageNumber="11" tableDoi="10.3897/jhr.72.39333.figures23-29">Figs 26</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="08381D7473C5096828B74A4ADFC21505" captionStart="Figures 23–29" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figures 23 - 29. Hybrizon xui sp. nov., ♀, paratype 23 habitus, lateral aspect 24 wings 25 hind tarsus, lateral aspect 26 head and mesosoma lateral aspect 27 head, anterior aspect 28 head and mesosoma, dorsal aspect 29 ovipositor and ovipositor sheath, lateral aspect." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.72.39333.figures23-29" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/351489" pageId="0" pageNumber="11" tableDoi="10.3897/jhr.72.39333.figures23-29">27</figureCitation>
), remainder of antenna largely dark brown; veins and pterostigma largely dark brown; vein 1-M of fore wing as dark as vein 2-CU1 of fore wing or nearly so; wing membrane subhyaline.
</paragraph>
<caption id="D2A6FF11F0BAA972C0C28F0C8626B2A5" doi="10.3897/jhr.72.39333.figures23-29" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/351489" pageId="0" pageNumber="11" start="Figures 23–29" startId="F4">
