<paragraph id="4A2A443326F01292C90DBEFEC4BB899E" pageId="0" pageNumber="11">
<emphasis id="3A551580E42F4743443A528E4FE069ED" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="11">
<emphasis id="5E762952BA00A0154FA79E8E7229022E" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="11">Variation</emphasis>
.
</emphasis>
Length of body (3.2
<normalizedToken id="51703290D06D1522BA9B8AA325E471F1" originalValue="–)3.6–">-)3.6-</normalizedToken>
4.5 mm, of fore wing 2.6-3.7 mm; maximum width of face 1.3-1.4 times its minimum width; basal cell of fore wing with 10-24 setae; anteriorly notaulic area of mesoscutum ivory or brownish yellow, rarely dark brown; in lateral view length of hind basitarsus 5.4-6.6 times its maximum width; pedicellus entirely brown or dark brown, rarely pale yellowish ventrally; apical half of fourth tergite dark brown to brownish yellow; hind leg brownish yellow to brown. One paratype has a transverse groove subbasally on the second tergite.
</paragraph>
